00052 void CCHPFileHeader::ParseString
00053 (
00054         TagValuePairTypeList &tagList,
00055         std::string sSource, 
00056         std::string sDelimiter1, 
00057         std::string sDelimiter2
00058 )
00059 {
00060         std::string buf;
00061         TagValuePairType param;
00062         std::list<std::string> delList;
00063         std::list<std::string> delList2;
00064 
00065         // Skip delimiters at beginning and find first "non-delimiter" (1st delimiter)
00066         std::string::size_type lastPos1 = sSource.find_first_not_of(sDelimiter1, 0);
00067         std::string::size_type pos1     = sSource.find_first_of(sDelimiter1, lastPos1);
00068 
00069         // Loop to get tokens
00070     while (std::string::npos != pos1 || std::string::npos != lastPos1)
00071         {               
00072                 // Get and store all parsed tokens
00073                 buf = sSource.substr(lastPos1, pos1 - lastPos1);
00074                 delList.push_back(buf);
00075 
00076                 // Skip delimiters and find next "non-delimiter" (1st delimiter)
00077                 lastPos1 = sSource.find_first_not_of(sDelimiter1, pos1);
00078                 pos1 = sSource.find_first_of(sDelimiter1, lastPos1);
00079         }
00080 
00081         // Reverse through stored tokens
00082         std::string sTemp;
00083         std::list<std::string>::reverse_iterator rev(delList.end());
00084         std::list<std::string>::reverse_iterator rev_end(delList.begin());
00085         for (; rev != rev_end; ++rev)
00086         {
00087                 buf = (*rev);
00088 
00089                 // Make sure "buf" has 2nd delimiter, otherwise add to previous "buf"
00090                 std::string::size_type posTemp = buf.find_first_of(sDelimiter2, 0);
00091                 if (std::string::npos == posTemp)
00092                 {
00093                         // Need to add the 1st delimiter back in the front of the "buf"
00094                         // Don't know how many delimiters to add, so let's just add one
00095                         buf = sDelimiter1 + buf;
00096                         sTemp = buf + sTemp;
00097                 }
00098                 else
00099                 {
00100                         // Finally store the valid "name=value" token
00101                         buf += sTemp;
00102                         delList2.push_back(buf);
00103                         sTemp = "";
00104                 }
00105         }
00106 
00107         // Now lets finally iterate over tokens to parse the "name" and "value"
00108         std::list<std::string>::iterator iter;
00109         for (iter=delList2.begin(); iter!=delList2.end(); ++iter)
00110         {
00111                 buf = (*iter);
00112 
00113                 // Skip delimiters at beginning and find first "non-delimiter" (2nd delimiter)
00114                 std::string::size_type lastPos2 = buf.find_first_not_of(sDelimiter2, 0);
00115                 std::string::size_type pos2     = buf.find_first_of(sDelimiter2, lastPos2);
00116                 
00117                 // Validate before assigning "Tag"
00118                 if (std::string::npos != pos2 || std::string::npos != lastPos2)
00119                 {
00120                         param.Tag = buf.substr(lastPos2, pos2 - lastPos2);
00121                         param.Value = "";
00122 
00123                         // Skip delimiters and find next "non-delimiter" (2nd delimiter)
00124                         lastPos2 = buf.find_first_not_of(sDelimiter2, pos2);
00125                         pos2 = buf.find_first_of(sDelimiter2, lastPos2);
00126 
00127                         // Validate before assigning "Value"
00128                         if (std::string::npos != pos2 || std::string::npos != lastPos2)
00129                                 param.Value = buf.substr(lastPos2, pos2 - lastPos2);
00130 
00131                         // Add to tag list
00132                         tagList.push_back(param);
00133                 }
00134         }
00135 }

00464 bool CCHPFileData::Open(bool bReadHeaderOnly)
00465 {
00466         bool retVal = false;
00467 
00468         // Open the file.
00469         std::ifstream instr;
00470         bool bXDA = false;
00471         if (IsXDACompatibleFile())
00472                 bXDA = true;
00473         instr.open(m_FileName.c_str(), std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
00474 
00475         // Check if open
00476         if (!instr)
00477         {
00478                 m_strError = "Unable to open the file.";
00479                 return false;
00480         }
00481 
00482 
00483         // Read the header
00484         if (bXDA)
00485         {
00486                 int32_t magic;
00487                 int32_t version;
00488                 int32_t ival;
00489                 uint16_t usval;
00490                 char *sval=NULL;
00491                 float fval;
00492                 uint8_t ucval;
00493 
00494 
00495                 // Read the magic number.
00496                 ReadInt32_I(instr, magic);
00497                 m_Header.m_Magic = magic;
00498 
00499                 // Check if new type.
00500                 if (magic != CHP_FILE_MAGIC_NUMBER)
00501                 {
00502                         m_strError = "The file does not appear to be the correct format.";
00503                         return false;
00504                 }
00505 
00506                 // Read the version
00507                 ReadInt32_I(instr, version);
00508                 m_Header.m_Version = version;
00509 
00510                 // Check for version 1 or 2
00511                 if (version > CHP_FILE_VERSION_NUMBER)
00512                 {
00513                         m_strError = "Unable to read this version of the CHP file.";
00514                         return false;
00515                 }
00516 
00517                 // Get the dimensions of the array
00518                 ReadUInt16_I(instr, usval);
00519                 m_Header.m_Cols=usval;
00520                 ReadUInt16_I(instr, usval);
00521                 m_Header.m_Rows=usval;
00522 
00523                 // Number of probe sets.
00524                 ReadInt32_I(instr, ival);
00525                 m_Header.m_NumProbeSets = ival;
00526                 ReadInt32_I(instr, ival); // no qc data extracted.
00527 
00528                 // Assay type
00529                 ReadInt32_I(instr, ival);
00530                 m_Header.m_AssayType = (CCHPFileHeader::GeneChipAssayType)ival;
00531 
00532                 // Prog ID.
00533                 ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00534                 m_Header.m_ProgID = sval;
00535                 delete[] sval;
00536 
00537                 // Parent cell file.
00538                 ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00539                 m_Header.m_ParentCellFile = sval;
00540                 delete[] sval;
00541 
00542                 // Chip type
00543                 ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00544                 m_Header.m_ChipType = sval;
00545                 delete[] sval;
00546 
00547                 // Algorithm
00548                 ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00549                 m_Header.m_AlgorithmName = sval;
00550                 delete[] sval;
00551 
00552                 // Algorithm version
00553                 ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00554                 m_Header.m_AlgorithmVersion = sval;
00555                 delete[] sval;
00556 
00557                 // Algorithm parameters.
00558                 int32_t nParams=0;
00559                 int32_t iParam;
00560                 ReadInt32_I(instr, nParams);
00561                 TagValuePairType param;
00562                 for (iParam=0; iParam<nParams; iParam++)
00563                 {
00564                         ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00565                         param.Tag = sval;
00566                         delete[] sval;
00567 
00568                         ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00569                         param.Value = sval;
00570                         delete[] sval;
00571 
00572                         m_Header.m_AlgorithmParameters.push_back(param);
00573                 }
00574 
00575                 // Summary parameters
00576                 ReadInt32_I(instr, nParams);
00577                 for (iParam=0; iParam<nParams; iParam++)
00578                 {
00579                         ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00580                         param.Tag = sval;
00581                         delete[] sval;
00582 
00583                         ReadCString_I(instr, sval);
00584                         param.Value = sval;
00585                         delete[] sval;
00586 
00587                         m_Header.m_SummaryParameters.push_back(param);
00588                 }
00589 
00590 
00591                 // Background info              
00592                 ReadInt32_I(instr, nParams);
00593                 m_Header.m_BackgroundZoneInfo.number_zones = nParams;
00594                 ReadFloat_I(instr, fval);

00596

00604                         zone.centery = fval;
00605                         ReadFloat_I(instr, fval);
00606                         zone.background = fval;
00607 
00608                         m_Header.m_BackgroundZoneInfo.zones.push_back(zone);
00609                 }
00610 
00611                 // Return if only reading the header.
00612                 if (bReadHeaderOnly == true)
00613                         return true;

00615

00618                         m_Header.m_AssayType != CCHPFileHeader::Genotyping &&
00619                         m_Header.m_AssayType != CCHPFileHeader::Universal &&
00620                         m_Header.m_AssayType != CCHPFileHeader::Resequencing)
00621                 {

00632                         ReadInt32_I(instr, ival);
00633

00667                                 if (analysisType == EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_STAT_ANALYSIS)

01325                                 ReadInt16_I(instr, i16);
01326                         }
01327 
01328                         ReadInt32_I(instr, i32);
01329                         if (i32>0)
01330                         {
01331                                 ReadFixedString(instr, str, i32);
01332                                 ReadInt32_I(instr, i32);
01333                                 if (i32>0)
01334                                         ReadFixedString(instr, str, i32);
01335                         }

01337                         for (index=0; index<dataSize; index++)
01338                         {
01339                                 ReadFloat_I(instr, score);
01340                                 m_ReseqResults.SetScore(index, score);
01341                         }
01342                 }

01351 
01352 bool CCHPFileData::IsXDACompatibleFile()
01353 {
01354         // Open the file.
01355         std::ifstream instr(m_FileName.c_str(), std::ios::in | std::ios::binary);
01356         if (!instr)
01357                 return false;
01358 
01359         // Read the magic number from the file.
01360         int32_t magic=0;
01361         ReadInt32_I(instr, magic);
01362         bool bXDAFile = (magic == CHP_FILE_MAGIC_NUMBER);
01363         instr.close();
01364 
01365         return bXDAFile;
01366 }

01370 bool CCHPFileData::IsMas5File()
01371 {
01372         // Open the file.
